<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 04 at 5:57PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Peach
and Houston Counties through 630 PM EDT...
At 557 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was centered 3 miles northwest
of Perry, moving southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Perry, Warner Robins, Unadilla, Hayneville, Meadowdale, Sand Bed,
Houston Lake, Grovania, Elko, Grove Park, Moss Oak, Henderson,
Kathleen, Klondike and Clinchfield.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
